VALUES
(44, 20, 21, 44, 11, 18, 18, 'repentance toward God', 'Repentance Granted to Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of repentance, specifically mentioning its importance for both Jews and Gentiles. Acts 20:21 speaks of ''repentance toward God,'' while Acts 11:18 highlights that God granted ''repentance unto life'' to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 21, 62, 5, 11, 13, 'faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Faith and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faith toward Jesus Christ as essential for eternal life. Acts 20:21 speaks of faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ, while 1 John 5:11-13 states that having the Son equates to having life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 21, 42, 13, 3, 3, 'repentance toward God', 'Connection of Repentance and Perishing', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of repentance. Acts 20:21 speaks of repentance toward God, while Luke 13:3 warns that without repentance, one will perish. This connection highlights the urgency of turning to God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 21, 42, 24, 47, 47, 'repentance toward God', 'Connection of Repentance and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of repentance toward God and the preaching of repentance among all nations. Acts 20:21 mentions ''repentance toward God,'' while Luke 24:47 speaks of ''repentance and remission of sins'' being preached. This connection highlights a shared theme of repentance in the context of faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 21, 47, 7, 10, 10, 'repentance toward God', 'Repentance and Sorrow Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of repentance, with Acts 20:21 highlighting ''repentance toward God'' and 2 Corinthians 7:10 discussing ''godly sorrow worketh repentance.'' This connection highlights the transformative nature of true repentance in relation to salvation.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 21, 55, 2, 25, 26, 'repentance toward God', 'Connection of Repentance and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of repentance, with Acts 20:21 highlighting ''repentance toward God'' and 2 Timothy 2:25 mentioning ''repentance to the acknowledging of the truth.'' This connection highlights the importance of turning towards God and recognizing truth as essential for spiritual recovery.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 59, 4, 14, 14, 'not knowing the things that shall befall me there', 'Uncertainty of Life''s Future', 'This connection highlights the uncertainty of future events in both passages. Acts 20:22 expresses a lack of knowledge about what will happen in Jerusalem, while James 4:14 emphasizes that life is unpredictable and fleeting.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 47, 5, 14, 14, 'bound in the spirit', 'Connection of Divine Motivation', 'This connection highlights the theme of being compelled by a higher purpose. In Acts, the phrase ''bound in the spirit'' suggests a strong inner drive, similar to how ''the love of Christ constraineth us'' indicates a powerful motivation in 2 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 42, 18, 31, 33, NULL, 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize a journey to Jerusalem, highlighting the significance of this location in the unfolding events. Acts 20:22 mentions being ''bound in the spirit'' to go to Jerusalem, while Luke 18:31 states, ''we go up to Jerusalem,'' indicating a pivotal moment in their missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 61, 1, 14, 14, 'bound in the spirit', 'Bound in Spirit and Departure', 'This connection highlights the theme of impending departure in both passages. Paul expresses his uncertainty about what awaits him in Jerusalem, while Peter acknowledges his imminent death, both indicating a sense of urgency and divine direction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 42, 9, 51, 51, NULL, 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize a determined journey to Jerusalem. Acts 20:22 speaks of being ''bound in the spirit,'' while Luke 9:51 describes setting one''s face to go to Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 43, 18, 4, 4, 'bound in the spirit', 'Bound in Spirit and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of foreknowledge and determination in both passages. Paul is ''bound in the spirit'' to go to Jerusalem, while Jesus ''knowing all things'' goes forth to meet his captors.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 22, 44, 17, 16, 16, 'bound in the spirit', 'Paul''s Stirred Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s emotional state and spiritual urgency. In Acts 20:22, he is ''bound in the spirit,'' while in Acts 17:16, his ''spirit was stirred'' by the idolatry he witnessed.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 23, 44, 9, 16, 16, 'bonds and afflictions abide me', 'Suffering for Christ''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering that accompanies the calling of Paul. Acts 20:23 mentions ''bonds and afflictions'' awaiting him, while Acts 9:16 states he must suffer ''for my name’s sake.''', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 23, 44, 21, 4, 4, 'bonds and afflictions abide me', 'Connection of Paul''s Journey Warnings', 'This connection highlights the theme of warnings Paul receives regarding his journey. In Acts 20:23, he acknowledges that ''bonds and afflictions abide me,'' while in Acts 21:4, disciples warn him through the Spirit not to go to Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 23, 52, 3, 3, 3, 'afflictions abide me', 'Afflictions and Appointments', 'This connection highlights the theme of afflictions faced by believers. Both passages emphasize that bonds and afflictions are expected in the Christian life.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 23, 55, 2, 12, 12, 'bonds and afflictions abide me', 'Suffering and Reigning Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering as a precursor to reward. Acts 20:23 mentions ''bonds and afflictions,'' while 2 Timothy 2:12 states, ''if we suffer, we shall also reign with him.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 23, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'bonds and afflictions abide me', 'Peace Amidst Tribulation', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of afflictions and tribulation faced by believers. Acts 20:23 mentions ''bonds and afflictions,'' while John 16:33 acknowledges ''tribulation'' in the world, yet both encourage perseverance and hope.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 55, 4, 6, 8, 'finish my course', 'Completion of Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of finishing one''s course in faith and ministry. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy, while 2 Timothy 4:6-8 reflects on having finished the course and kept the faith.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 47, 4, 1, 1, 'the ministry, which I have received', 'Ministry and Perseverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment to ministry and the importance of perseverance in fulfilling it. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy, while 2 Corinthians 4:1 highlights not fainting in the ministry received.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 47, 12, 10, 10, 'finish my course with joy', 'Strength in Weakness', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of enduring hardships for the sake of the ministry. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy despite challenges, while 2 Corinthians 12:10 highlights finding strength in weakness during trials for Christ''s sake.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 46, 15, 58, 58, 'none of these things move me', 'Steadfastness in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being steadfast and committed to the work of the Lord. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy, while 1 Corinthians 15:58 encourages believers to be unmoveable in their labor.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 44, 21, 13, 13, 'to testify the gospel of the grace of God', 'Paul''s Commitment to His Mission', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s readiness to face suffering for the gospel. In Acts 20:24, he expresses his determination to finish his ministry, while in Acts 21:13, he declares his willingness to die for the name of the Lord Jesus.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 50, 3, 13, 15, 'finish my course with joy', 'Pursuit of Spiritual Goals', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of pressing forward in one''s spiritual journey. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy, while Philippians 3:13-15 encourages forgetting the past and reaching for the prize ahead.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 24, 58, 12, 1, 3, 'finish my course with joy', 'Running the Race of Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of perseverance in ministry and faith. Acts 20:24 speaks of finishing the course with joy, while Hebrews 12:1-3 encourages running the race with patience, looking to Jesus for strength.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 44, 28, 31, 31, 'preaching the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Preaching the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize ''preaching the kingdom of God.'' The first passage reflects on the end of Paul''s preaching to a specific audience, while the second shows his continued ministry in Rome, highlighting the ongoing nature of his mission.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 40, 4, 23, 23, 'preaching the kingdom of God', 'Preaching the Kingdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of preaching the kingdom of God. In Acts, Paul acknowledges his preaching, while in Matthew, Jesus actively teaches and preaches the gospel of the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 44, 20, 38, 38, 'see my face no more', 'Emotional Farewell of Paul', 'Both passages emphasize the sorrow of the people as they realize they will not see Paul again. The phrase ''see my face no more'' in the source verse directly correlates with their grief in the target passage.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 40, 4, 17, 17, 'kingdom of God', 'Connection of Kingdom Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the preaching of the kingdom. Acts 20:25 refers to preaching the kingdom of God, while Matthew 4:17 announces that the kingdom of heaven is at hand.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 42, 9, 60, 60, 'preaching the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Preaching the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of preaching the kingdom of God. In Acts, Paul acknowledges he will no longer see those he preached to, while in Luke, Jesus instructs to prioritize preaching the kingdom over personal matters.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 42, 16, 16, 16, 'kingdom of God', 'Connection of Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the preaching of the kingdom of God. Acts 20:25 reflects Paul''s ministry, while Luke 16:16 marks the beginning of this proclamation since John.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 25, 45, 15, 23, 23, 'see my face no more', 'Desire for Future Fellowship', 'This connection highlights the longing for community and fellowship in both passages. In Acts, the speaker acknowledges they will not see the audience again, while in Romans, there is a desire to visit and connect with others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 44, 18, 6, 6, NULL, 'Responsibility for Spiritual Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the speaker''s purity from the blood of others, indicating a clear stance on spiritual accountability. In Acts 20:26, the speaker asserts being ''pure from the blood of all men,'' while in Acts 18:6, he declares, ''I am clean,'' suggesting a similar theme of responsibility for the message delivered.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 26, 3, 18, 21, 'pure from the blood of all men', 'Responsibility for Warning Others', 'Both passages emphasize the responsibility of individuals to warn others about their wickedness. Acts 20:26 reflects a sense of accountability for one''s actions, paralleling Ezekiel 3:18-21, which states that failing to warn the wicked results in blood being required at one''s hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 26, 33, 2, 9, 'pure from the blood of all men', 'Responsibility of the Watchman', 'Both passages emphasize the accountability of a watchman to warn others. In Acts, Paul declares he is ''pure from the blood of all men,'' indicating he has fulfilled his duty to warn. Similarly, Ezekiel stresses that the watchman must sound the alarm to prevent the blood of the people from being required at his hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 43, 12, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Witness and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing record and accountability. In Acts, the speaker asserts purity from the blood of all men, indicating a responsibility to witness, while in John, the people bear record of Jesus'' miracle, emphasizing their role in testifying to his works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 10, 3, 28, 28, NULL, 'Guiltlessness from Bloodshed', 'This connection highlights the theme of being guiltless regarding bloodshed. Both Paul and David assert their innocence concerning the blood of others, emphasizing accountability and purity in their leadership.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 18, 16, 19, 19, NULL, 'Witness and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of personal accountability and testimony. Both passages emphasize the idea of having a record or witness regarding one''s actions and integrity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 26, 43, 19, 35, 35, NULL, 'Connection of Witness and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing witness and accountability. In Acts, the speaker asserts purity from the blood of all men, while in John, the emphasis is on the truth of the witness provided.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 44, 20, 20, 20, NULL, 'Declaration of God''s Counsel', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment to sharing all that is beneficial. Acts 20:27 states the declaration of God''s counsel, while Acts 20:20 highlights the teaching of what is profitable.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 52, 2, 4, 4, 'all the counsel of God', 'Proclaiming God''s Counsel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of declaring God''s message faithfully. Acts 20:27 speaks of declaring ''all the counsel of God,'' while 1 Thessalonians 2:4 highlights speaking as entrusted with the gospel, aiming to please God rather than men.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 47, 4, 2, 2, 'all the counsel of God', 'Truth and Transparency in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the importance of declaring the truth and integrity in handling God''s word. Both passages emphasize a commitment to honesty and transparency in ministry, rejecting deceitful practices.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 48, 1, 7, 10, 'declare unto you all the counsel of God', 'Proclamation of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of declaring the true gospel without alteration. Acts 20:27''s declaration of ''all the counsel of God'' resonates with Galatians 1:7-10''s warning against perverting the gospel.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 48, 4, 16, 16, 'all the counsel of God', 'Truth and Counsel Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of truth-telling in both passages. In Acts, declaring ''all the counsel of God'' suggests a commitment to truth, while in Galatians, the speaker questions if they have become an ''enemy'' for speaking the truth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 19, 32, 11, 11, NULL, 'Joy in God''s Counsel', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejoicing in the Lord as a response to receiving His counsel. Both passages emphasize the importance of being upright in heart and the joy that comes from understanding God''s guidance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 27, 24, 23, 22, 22, 'counsel of God', 'Counsel of God and Prophetic Duty', 'This connection highlights the importance of declaring God''s counsel. Both passages emphasize the necessity of sharing God''s words to lead people away from evil.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 60, 5, 2, 3, 'feed the church of God', 'Connection of Oversight and Feeding', 'Both passages emphasize the responsibility to ''feed the flock of God'' and provide oversight. They highlight the importance of serving willingly and being examples to the church.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 54, 4, 16, 16, NULL, 'Call to Vigilance in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of taking heed to oneself and the community. Acts 20:28 focuses on the responsibility of overseers to care for the church, while 1 Timothy 4:16 highlights the necessity of personal vigilance and sound doctrine for the benefit of oneself and others.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'feed the church of God', 'Shepherding and Feeding the Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a shepherd in caring for the flock. Acts 20:28 speaks of feeding the church, while Isaiah 40:11 describes how the shepherd feeds and gathers the lambs.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 60, 1, 18, 19, 'purchased with his own blood', 'Redemption through Christ''s Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the blood in the context of redemption and the church. Acts 20:28 speaks of the church purchased with blood, while 1 Peter 1:18-19 highlights redemption through the precious blood of Christ.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 54, 3, 2, 2, 'overseers, to feed the church', 'Leadership and Oversight in the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the role of church leaders. Acts 20:28 speaks of overseers tasked with feeding the church, while 1 Timothy 3:2 outlines the qualifications for a bishop, highlighting the importance of their character and responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 24, 3, 15, 15, 'feed the church of God', 'Connection of Pastors and Oversight', 'Both passages emphasize the role of leaders in providing spiritual nourishment. Acts 20:28 speaks of overseers feeding the church, while Jeremiah 3:15 mentions pastors feeding with knowledge and understanding.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 28, 44, 13, 2, 2, 'the Holy Ghost', 'Role of the Holy Ghost', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Ghost in guiding and appointing leaders within the church. Both passages emphasize the importance of the Holy Ghost in overseeing and calling individuals for ministry.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 40, 7, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of False Prophets and Wolves', 'Both passages emphasize the danger posed by false leaders, described as ''grievous wolves'' and ''ravening wolves.'' This connection highlights the need for vigilance against those who appear benign but seek to harm the faithful.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 61, 2, 1, 1, 'not sparing the flock', 'Warning Against False Teachers', 'This connection highlights the presence of false teachers and their destructive impact on the community. Both passages emphasize the danger posed by those who do not spare the flock and introduce heresies.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 42, 10, 3, 3, 'wolves', 'Lambs and Wolves Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of ''wolves'' threatening the ''flock'' or ''lambs.'' This connection highlights the danger faced by believers in their mission and the need for vigilance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 43, 10, 12, 12, 'grievous wolves', 'Connection of Wolves and Shepherds', 'Both passages emphasize the danger posed by wolves to the flock. Acts 20:29 warns of ''grievous wolves'' entering, while John 10:12 describes a wolf that scatters the sheep, highlighting the threat to the community.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 44, 20, 28, 28, 'the flock', 'Warning and Responsibility for Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance among church leaders. Acts 20:28 calls them to care for the flock, while Acts 20:29 warns of ''grievous wolves'' that threaten it.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 40, 10, 16, 16, 'wolves', 'Wolves and Sheep Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of wolves threatening the flock of sheep. Acts warns of grievous wolves entering, while Matthew depicts the disciples as sheep among wolves, highlighting the danger they face.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 29, 24, 23, 1, 1, 'not sparing the flock', 'Wolves and Scattering Sheep', 'This connection highlights the theme of danger to the flock. Both passages emphasize the destruction and scattering of sheep, indicating a warning against harmful leaders.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 54, 1, 19, 20, 'draw away disciples after them', 'False Teachers and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the emergence of false teachers in both passages. Acts 20:30 warns of men arising to draw away disciples, while 1 Timothy 1:19-20 mentions individuals who have deviated from faith, leading to severe consequences.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 55, 4, 3, 4, 'draw away disciples after them', 'Connection of False Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the rise of false teachers who lead others away from sound doctrine. Acts 20:30 warns of men arising to draw away disciples, while 2 Timothy 4:3-4 describes people seeking teachers that cater to their desires, turning from the truth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 20, 23, 33, 33, 'speaking perverse things', 'Connection of Perverse Things', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of perverse things arising from within, leading individuals astray. Acts warns of men speaking perverse things, while Proverbs highlights the heart uttering perverse things.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 62, 2, 19, 19, 'to draw away disciples after them', 'Connection of Deception and Departure', 'Both passages emphasize the emergence of individuals who lead others away from the truth. Acts 20:30 warns of men arising to draw away disciples, while 1 John 2:19 describes those who left the community, revealing they were not truly part of it.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 20, 19, 1, 1, 'perverse things', 'Integrity vs. Perverse Speech', 'This connection highlights the contrast between integrity and perverse speech. Acts 20:30 warns against those who speak perverse things, while Proverbs 19:1 emphasizes the value of integrity over perverse lips.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 44, 11, 26, 26, 'draw away disciples after them', 'Disciples and False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the emergence of false teachings as a threat to the community of believers. In Acts 20:30, the warning about men arising to draw away disciples relates to the establishment of the disciples in Antioch, where they were first called Christians, emphasizing the importance of sound teaching.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 30, 23, 59, 3, 3, 'speaking perverse things', 'Connection of Perversion and Deceit', 'This connection highlights the theme of speaking ''perverse things'' in Acts 20:30 and ''perverseness'' in Isaiah 59:3. Both passages emphasize the danger of deceitful speech leading others astray.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 44, 19, 8, 8, 'the space of three years', 'Duration of Ministry Emphasis', 'Both passages emphasize the duration of ministry, with ''the space of three years'' in Acts 20:31 and ''the space of three months'' in Acts 19:8. This connection highlights the commitment and persistence in preaching the kingdom of God over extended periods.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 44, 20, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Tears and Humility', 'Both passages emphasize the emotional weight of Paul''s ministry, highlighting his service with ''many tears'' and his warning with ''tears.'' This connection underscores the depth of his commitment and the struggles he faced.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 51, 1, 28, 28, NULL, 'Warning and Teaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of warning every person. Acts 20:31 highlights the emotional commitment to this warning, while Colossians 1:28 connects it to teaching and presenting individuals perfect in Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 58, 13, 17, 17, NULL, 'Leadership and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of leaders who watch over their followers. Acts 20:31 highlights the emotional investment of leaders, while Hebrews 13:17 stresses the accountability of those leaders for the souls they oversee.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 26, 3, 17, 20, 'watch, and remember', 'Warning and Watchfulness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of warning others about their wickedness. Acts 20:31 reflects Paul''s dedication to warning others, paralleling Ezekiel''s role as a watchman tasked with delivering warnings from God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 40, 13, 25, 25, 'watch', 'Vigilance Against Spiritual Threats', 'This connection highlights the theme of vigilance in both passages. Acts 20:31 emphasizes the need to ''watch'' and be alert, while Matthew 13:25 illustrates the danger of the enemy''s actions occurring while men are ''asleep.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 31, 42, 21, 36, 36, 'watch', 'Call to Vigilance and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of vigilance and prayer. Acts 20:31''s call to ''watch'' parallels Luke 21:36''s exhortation to ''watch'' and ''pray always,'' highlighting a shared theme of spiritual preparedness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 32, 51, 1, 12, 12, 'inheritance among all them which are sanctified', 'Inheritance Among the Sanctified', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inheritance among the sanctified. Acts 20:32 speaks of an inheritance among those sanctified, while Colossians 1:12 refers to being partakers of the inheritance of the saints in light.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
